            "questionText": "Calculate the induced electromotive force $!$E$!$ (in volts) generated during regenerative braking in a modern electric vehicle. Assume the following formula applies: $!$E = N \\cdot B \\cdot \\ell \\cdot v$!$, where $!$N$!$ is the number of turns in the coil, $!$B$!$ is the magnetic flux density (in tesla), $!$\\ell$!$ is the effective length of the conductor within the magnetic field (in meters), and $!$v$!$ is the relative speed between the conductor and the magnetic field (in meters per second). Provide a single numerical value for $!$E$!$. (If any values are missing, please supply them.)",
